WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
NVIDIA reporting a record earnings and revenue last night, reporting an 85% increase in revenue,

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.560
a 92% increase in data center revenue. NVIDIA founder and CEO Jensen Huang told me in part

00:00:12.560 --> 00:00:19.360
two of my interview, the data center rollout is accelerating and AI is also assisting in America's

00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:27.600
national security. You find yourself not only the face of incredible growth and new technology

00:00:27.600 --> 00:00:33.440
in the world, but also in the middle of the potential national security concerns between

00:00:33.440 --> 00:00:35.640
the U.S.-China relationship.

00:00:35.640 --> 00:00:37.500
So what do you want to say about that?

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:43.480
Because critics would say that selling advance chips to China helps China close the gap and

00:00:43.480 --> 00:00:49.520
perhaps beat the U.S. in AI, which of course the president has said many times wants

00:00:49.520 --> 00:00:52.120
to own it and win it.

00:00:52.120 --> 00:00:56.160
And yet the other angle is the fact that if we block all sales, then China does

00:00:56.160 --> 00:00:57.520
it anyway.

00:00:57.520 --> 00:01:00.920
accelerating the growth coming out of companies like Huawei.

00:01:02.130 --> 00:01:07.810
I think you've summarized it really well. The president would like us to win in every aspect

00:01:07.810 --> 00:01:16.290
of AI. Remember, Nvidia is AI. And the reason we're part of the AI industry, AI is a five-layer

00:01:16.290 --> 00:01:24.210
cake. It includes energy and chips, infrastructure, models, and then the applications that run on top.

00:01:24.210 --> 00:01:31.650
The United States has to be absolutely certain and determined to lead the world in every

00:01:31.650 --> 00:01:38.530
aspect, every layer of that five-layer cake—from energy, of course, from chips, of course.

00:01:38.530 --> 00:01:44.690
And so all of these five layers are part of the new AI industry.

00:01:44.690 --> 00:01:49.330
The president has been very clear he would like NVIDIA to, on the one hand, make sure

00:01:49.330 --> 00:01:56.050
that American technology and American companies have the benefit of the latest of NVIDIA,

00:01:56.050 --> 00:01:59.250
and the most of NVIDIA, and that's surely the case.

00:01:59.250 --> 00:02:03.850
He's been very clear that he would like American companies to win around the world.

00:02:03.850 --> 00:02:09.250
Winning around the world allows us to, one, export, generate revenues for the country, bring

00:02:09.250 --> 00:02:13.370
back tax dollars for the country, create jobs in America.

00:02:13.370 --> 00:02:19.410
It allows us also to diffuse and spread the American technology stack around the world

00:02:19.410 --> 00:02:23.730
so that the rest of the world can be built on top of American technology and standards.

00:02:23.730 --> 00:02:26.010
And so he's been very clear about that.

00:02:26.010 --> 00:02:30.890
With respect to national security, China obviously has all the chips they need.

00:02:30.890 --> 00:02:33.210
That's the reason why they don't need ours.

00:02:33.210 --> 00:02:35.410
And Huawei has done a very good job.

00:02:35.410 --> 00:02:38.230
They're obviously one of the largest companies in the world.

00:02:38.230 --> 00:02:40.730
They had a record year.

00:02:40.730 --> 00:02:43.610
They're flourishing in our absence.

00:02:43.610 --> 00:02:49.210
And they're now exporting their technology out to the rest of the world, competing

00:02:49.210 --> 00:02:51.850
with American companies around the world.

00:02:51.850 --> 00:02:56.410
So I think that their ability to secure technology

00:02:56.410 --> 00:02:58.290
for their national security reasons,

00:02:58.290 --> 00:03:04.770
I think they have more than ample for their own needs.

00:03:04.770 --> 00:03:06.490
Well, Jensen, this is all happening

00:03:06.490 --> 00:03:09.690
at a time that the US military is increasingly

00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:12.730
in need of AI chips as well.

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:15.370
And I mean, here we are in the middle of a war.

00:03:15.370 --> 00:03:19.010
And I know that many of the rescues and the Operation

00:03:19.010 --> 00:03:26.890
Epic Fury is relying on AI-enabled surveillance, satellite imagery, drones, signal processing,

00:03:26.890 --> 00:03:31.650
high-performance computing systems where you're number one.

00:03:31.650 --> 00:03:33.090
So tell me a little about that.

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:37.730
Without giving us any secrets, obviously, Jensen, about this great nation, can you talk to us

00:03:37.730 --> 00:03:43.410
a little about, for example, when we were locating that missing officer in the mountainous

00:03:43.410 --> 00:03:50.610
terrain of Iran, how envidia chips were actually critical in that regard in terms of surveillance

00:03:50.610 --> 00:03:52.810
and finding our man?

00:03:52.810 --> 00:03:59.370
Well we do a lot of work in imaging and most of the world's radar systems and imaging

00:03:59.370 --> 00:04:08.890
systems has envidia chips in it and we're just incredibly honored to be able to support

00:04:08.890 --> 00:04:17.010
our nation. Recently, you might have seen an announcement where the Department of War has

00:04:17.010 --> 00:04:21.530
access to NVIDIA's technology so that they – and our technology is completely open

00:04:21.530 --> 00:04:28.410
source so that it could be modified and enhanced for the applications of our military. And

00:04:28.410 --> 00:04:35.410
we have great partnerships across the ecosystem of contractors and technology companies that

00:04:35.410 --> 00:04:42.090
service the national securities organizations around in our country and so it's a great

00:04:42.090 --> 00:04:44.050
honor for us to be able to do that.

00:04:44.050 --> 00:04:48.770
And so technology matters in the future of national security and we're delighted to

00:04:48.770 --> 00:04:49.770
be part of that.

00:04:49.770 --> 00:04:51.290
Well, that's right, Jensen.

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:56.730
And I know that people view NVIDIA no longer as just an innovative technology company,

00:04:56.730 --> 00:05:04.330
but as a critical national security infrastructure base for the U.S. government.

00:05:04.330 --> 00:05:06.930
Is that a fair statement?

00:05:06.930 --> 00:05:09.690
Well, we're a very large technology company,

00:05:09.690 --> 00:05:13.130
and we're an American technology company.

00:05:13.130 --> 00:05:16.450
We want America's technology industry

00:05:16.450 --> 00:05:19.450
to be a national treasure of the United States.

00:05:19.450 --> 00:05:23.450
We participate in every aspect of industry,

00:05:23.450 --> 00:05:26.090
including building the AI industry itself.

00:05:26.090 --> 00:05:28.490
One of the things that's really incredible

00:05:28.490 --> 00:05:31.770
is that because of the buildout of AI,

00:05:31.770 --> 00:05:34.490
the largest infrastructure build out in history.

00:05:34.490 --> 00:05:38.130
We're creating so many jobs inside the United States.

00:05:38.130 --> 00:05:42.010
Manufacturing chip plants, packaging plants,

00:05:42.010 --> 00:05:45.050
computer plants, and of course, these AI data centers.

00:05:45.050 --> 00:05:47.210
The number of jobs that we're creating

00:05:47.210 --> 00:05:52.210
in the manufacturing sector is largest in recent history.

00:05:52.890 --> 00:05:54.970
And so over the next several years,

00:05:54.970 --> 00:05:57.130
we're gonna see trillions of dollars investment

00:05:57.130 --> 00:05:59.210
coming back into the United States

00:05:59.210 --> 00:06:02.450
all driven because of the buildout of AI infrastructure.

00:06:02.450 --> 00:06:05.490
And so I'm really delighted to see this happening.

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:10.490
And it's going to be, of course, creating jobs,

00:06:10.490 --> 00:06:13.410
enhancing our manufacturing sector,

00:06:13.410 --> 00:06:16.130
reducing our dependence on other countries

00:06:16.130 --> 00:06:19.650
and manufacturing is a core part of our national security.

00:06:19.650 --> 00:06:21.890
And we play a very central role in doing that.

00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:23.170
Yeah, but at the same time,

00:06:23.170 --> 00:06:25.570
you're becoming more successful and growing

00:06:25.570 --> 00:06:28.490
and making more money and generating more revenue.

00:06:28.490 --> 00:06:34.950
you've got wannabes on your heels. How serious are the competitive threats right now when

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:43.170
you look at AMD or Google or Amazon, Trinium or Cerebrus and that very successful IPO the

00:06:43.170 --> 00:06:48.930
other day? How significant do you view all of these competitors lurking?

00:06:48.930 --> 00:06:54.010
We always take our competitors seriously. We're in the largest industry in the world

00:06:54.010 --> 00:06:59.210
And so I have more than more than enough competition for anybody to enjoy.

00:06:59.650 --> 00:07:05.850
And so, so, but the important thing is this, Maria, over the last year, we actually gain share.

00:07:06.450 --> 00:07:11.650
We gain share in AI, in the hyperscalers, in the model builders.

00:07:12.090 --> 00:07:19.050
And we created a whole new segment of data centers that is unique, requires the unique

00:07:19.050 --> 00:07:25.670
capability that NVIDIA has, and we're really the only company that's frontiering and bringing

00:07:25.670 --> 00:07:30.370
out physical AI for manufacturing and industrial applications.

00:07:30.370 --> 00:07:35.090
And so we're gaining share in this area as the market is actually expanding, so it's

00:07:35.090 --> 00:07:36.570
