00:09:36.610 --> 00:09:44.170
So I think it's a foregone conclusion at this point that the electricity industry, the internet

00:09:44.170 --> 00:09:50.170
industry that AI is built upon will be much larger than both of those industries previously.

00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:54.770
And so we're going to create a lot of manufacturing jobs and we're going to create a whole lot

00:09:54.770 --> 00:09:59.170
of different industries and companies on top of AI that the world's never even seen

00:09:59.170 --> 00:10:00.170
yet.

00:10:00.170 --> 00:10:02.810
And it's just an incredible privilege to be part of that.

00:10:02.810 --> 00:10:07.370
Well, Jensen, you made a great point just now, mentioned in Corning, and can you talk to

00:10:07.370 --> 00:10:12.570
us a word, give us a word on strategy, because you've made a number of partnership announcements

00:10:12.570 --> 00:10:14.810
and you've made a number of acquisitions as well.

00:10:14.810 --> 00:10:19.410
I mean, talking about all of this growth, you don't even, you know, look at the fact

00:10:19.410 --> 00:10:22.770
that you made the acquisition of Grok at the end of last year.

00:10:22.770 --> 00:10:24.770
I wonder what that was about.

00:10:24.770 --> 00:10:27.050
You know, what is the strategy there?

00:10:27.050 --> 00:10:28.610
Is it offense and defense?

00:10:28.610 --> 00:10:31.730
and then you look at things like Corning and Lumentum

00:10:31.730 --> 00:10:34.530
and you've been so ahead of the game

00:10:34.530 --> 00:10:37.490
