00:16:55.890 --> 00:16:57.650
That's a fantastic thing.

00:16:57.650 --> 00:16:59.210
The second thing is, with respect

00:16:59.210 --> 00:17:01.090
to all the information workers, AI

00:17:01.090 --> 00:17:05.050
will clearly augment your work.

00:17:05.050 --> 00:17:08.050
The way you work today is going to be very different than the past.

00:17:08.050 --> 00:17:11.890
Today, most of us are sitting in front of our computers typing all the time.

00:17:11.890 --> 00:17:15.570
If you just take a step back and think about what software engineers do,

00:17:15.570 --> 00:17:17.730
we spend all of our time typing.

00:17:17.730 --> 00:17:20.410
Well, you ought to be spending your time problem solving.

00:17:20.410 --> 00:17:22.690
And the way that people problem solve in the future,

00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:24.250
it's just going to be very different.

00:17:24.250 --> 00:17:28.170
And so we're still going to need just as many software engineers if not more.

00:17:28.170 --> 00:17:30.890
We're going to need more product engineers if not more.

00:17:30.890 --> 00:17:32.650
And so even more than that.

00:17:32.650 --> 00:17:36.090
And so the world's work is going to be very different.

00:17:36.090 --> 00:17:38.090
The one thing that I would advise young people,

00:17:38.090 --> 00:17:40.090
and I advise every one of them,

00:17:40.090 --> 00:17:43.330
you know, although some people say young workers,

00:17:43.330 --> 00:17:45.970
young college graduates will be the first

00:17:45.970 --> 00:17:47.410
to lose the opportunity,

00:17:47.410 --> 00:17:49.570
that 50% of their jobs will be gone.

00:17:49.570 --> 00:17:51.770
I think that's just complete nonsense.

00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:54.970
The young people who are graduating from school today

00:17:54.970 --> 00:17:56.930
are the best users of AI

00:17:56.930 --> 00:17:59.370
because they grew up in that era.

00:17:59.370 --> 00:18:01.130
When you're a great user of AI,

00:18:01.130 --> 00:18:04.210
you're going to be highly employable.

00:18:04.210 --> 00:18:05.690
You're not going to lose, a person

00:18:05.690 --> 00:18:08.290
sound not likely to lose your job to AI.

00:18:08.290 --> 00:18:10.090
You're going to lose your job to someone

00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:12.050
who is an expert in using AI.

00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:14.690
And so I would recommend that everybody

00:18:14.690 --> 00:18:16.410
learn how to use AI.

00:18:16.410 --> 00:18:19.170
And so for the doomers that are saying

00:18:19.170 --> 00:18:21.250
AI is destroying jobs, I think they're

00:18:21.250 --> 00:18:23.210
doing a disservice to society.

00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:25.570
AI is creating jobs.

00:18:25.570 --> 00:18:27.970
I think the doomers that are telling young people

00:18:27.970 --> 00:18:30.770
that AI is going to destroy opportunities for them,

00:18:30.770 --> 00:18:32.250
It's a disservice to them.

00:18:32.250 --> 00:18:35.610
We should encourage them, inspire them to engage AI,

00:18:35.610 --> 00:18:39.010
to become an expert in learning how to work with AI.

00:18:39.010 --> 00:18:42.210
And then lastly, all of the companies that I know

00:18:42.210 --> 00:18:45.050
who are using AI are running faster than ever.

00:18:45.050 --> 00:18:46.410
They're flying faster than ever.

00:18:46.410 --> 00:18:48.250
They're more ambitious than ever.

00:18:48.250 --> 00:18:51.770
And so I think the world's companies that use AI

00:18:51.770 --> 00:18:53.850
are going to be incredibly successful,

00:18:53.850 --> 00:18:56.250
which is the reason why we use so much of it here.

00:18:56.250 --> 00:18:58.450
Yeah, and I think that's great advice

00:18:58.450 --> 00:19:00.570
for our graduates of 2026.

00:19:00.570 --> 00:19:04.850
And it's this intelligence revolution is certainly making everyone smarter.

00:19:04.850 --> 00:19:09.990
I should point out that you've also been real shareholder friendly in terms of this quarter

00:19:09.990 --> 00:19:14.210
announcing the $80 billion share buyback plan and an increase in the dividend.

00:19:14.210 --> 00:19:18.030
Jensen, I want to congratulate you and thank you so much for spending the time with us.

00:19:18.030 --> 00:19:22.090
This was a comprehensive interview and I so appreciate you spending the time talking

00:19:22.090 --> 00:19:23.530
with our audience on this.

00:19:23.530 --> 00:19:25.030
Thank you, Jensen.

00:19:25.030 --> 00:19:26.030
Thank you, Maria.

00:19:26.030 --> 00:19:27.530
I always love talking to you.

00:19:27.530 --> 00:19:28.530
Good to see you.

00:19:28.530 --> 00:19:29.570
Jensen Huang joining us.

00:19:29.570 --> 00:19:31.570
CEO and founder at NVIDIA.

00:19:31.570 --> 00:19:32.570
We'll be right back.

